- "Resources" in this context refer to supplies, personnel, and equipment used in disaster response;
- "Zone" refers to a specific geographic area where the disaster occurred;
- "Disaster type" categorizes the nature of the disaster, such as fire, epidemic, or flood.

sql:
SELECT region_id, COUNT(disaster_id) AS disaster_count
FROM disasters
GROUP BY region_id;

SELECT MAX(disaster_count) AS highest_disaster_count
FROM (
  SELECT COUNT(disaster_id) AS disaster_count
  FROM disasters
  GROUP BY disaster_type_id
);

